President Joe Biden spoke with Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom to express his commitment to strengthening the special relationship between the two countries and revitalizing transatlantic ties. They emphasized the importance of NATO for collective defense and shared values. President Biden also highlighted the need for cooperation through multilateral organizations to address challenges such as climate change, COVID-19, and global health security. He expressed his readiness to work closely with Prime Minister Johnson as the UK hosts the G-7 and United Nations Climate Change Conference this year. The leaders also discussed the importance of coordination on foreign policy priorities, including China, Iran, and Russia.